HEADWORD: Crocin
<hw>Cro"cin</hw> <pr>(kr?"s?n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<?/<?/<?/<?/ saffron.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>The
coloring matter of Chinese yellow pods, the fruit of <spn>Gardenia
grandiflora</spn>.</def> <au>Watts.</au> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A red powder
(called also <altname>polychroite</altname>), which is made from the
saffron (<spn>Crocus sativus</spn>). See <er>Polychroite</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

